  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Engineer (C&S)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles & responsibilities:</strong></p><p>1. Coordination with Construction team/ Design Consultant/PE/construction subcontractor, etc. for Detail Design Development.</p><p>2. Carryout detailed analysis and design of civil, structural, and geotechnical works.</p><p>3. Prepare design calculation reports and structural drawings for authorities' submissions.</p><p>4. Planning relevant temporary civil structure, plan & section required for the Traffic diversion, such as Drain diversion, Retaining wall, shop drawing development.</p><p>5. Review and planning for ERSS system for Underground structure using Diaphragm wall such as KP, Decking, Strutting, decking, etc.</p><p>6. Check/Rectificationof all the structural drawing/ shop drawing if required.</p><p><strong>Requirements and relevant experience are as below:</strong></p><p>1. Bachelor’s / Master’s Degree of Civil Engineering or close discipline from a recognized Institution.</p><p>2. Strong engineering fundamental and analytical skills in geotechnical and structural analysis and design works is an advantage.</p><p>3. Good knowledge of the application of design and drafting software. </p><p>4. Minimum 5 years of experience in Civil and Structural Engineering especially for LTA\nProject.</p><p>5. Be well-aware of Traffic Diversion, Temp. Drain Diversion, and authority approval procedure.</p><p>6. Be well-aware of Underground Structure/Construction Sequences and related civil design works.</p><p>7. Be well-aware of Eurocode, LTA CDC, and relevant design specification/standards.</p><p>* Candidates who has experience as CS engineer (Design) in D&B contractor\nside would be an advantage.</p><p>* Interested applicants are required to submit their detailed CV and state their current and expected salary.</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
